channel.description:
Well, I want to make some competition to TheLetterQArousesMe's Allstar-scape server, so, for the first building blocks, I started a new dialogue system. This is my 2nd dialogue system ever, so it may be crappy.

[b][size=24pt]What makes this dialogue system different from a lot of others?[/size][/b]
This dialogue system uses variable arguments. A brief definition of variable arguments is [url=http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php?topic=552244.0]here[/url].

Okay, so let's start!

[hr]

Open up Client.java. Search for
[code=java]
void UpdateNpcChat
[/code]
Delete that whole entire void.

[b]Why?[/b] - Because we are replacing this dialogue system with another one!

Now, find
[code=java]
void process() {
[/code]
Inside this void, find:
[code=java]
if ((NpcDialogue > 0) && (NpcDialogueSend == false))
[/code]
You should see something like this:
[code=java]
		if ((NpcDialogue > 0) && (NpcDialogueSend == false))
			UpdateNPCChat();
[/code]
Remove that. Now (still in process), look for:
[code=java]
// Npc Talking
[/code]
You should see something like:
[code=java]
				// Npc Talking
				if (NpcDialogue > 0) {
					NpcDialogue = 0;
					NpcTalkTo = 0;
					NpcDialogueSend = false;
					RemoveAllWindows();
				}
[/code]
Remove that also.

[b]Why?[/b] - Process is a messy bunch of code in my opinion. The person who made Allstar didn't use the click here to continue packet (which is packet 40) wisely.

Now let's get out of process. Time to edit the packet! Look for:
[code=java]
case 40:
[/code]
After clicking enter 2 (or 3?) times, you'll see something like:
http://pastebin.com/fv3aZniX

That's one messy piece of clobber right? Well, I'd like you to replace that with this:
[code=java]
		case 40:
			println_debug("Unhandled packet [" + packetType + ", InterFaceId: "
					+ inStream.readUnsignedWordA() + ", size=" + packetSize
					+ "]: ]" + misc.Hex(inStream.buffer, 1, packetSize) + "[");
			println_debug("Action Button: "
					+ misc.HexToInt(inStream.buffer, 0, packetSize));
			break;
[/code]

[b]Why?[/b] - As I said before, the owner of Allstar-scape did not use this packet wisely. He just made a bunch of junk in this packet that could be handled.
[b]NOTE:[/b] - [b]This will be edited later in the tutorial![/b]

Okay, next, I'd like you to make a folder. Name is dialogue. Call this the 'dialogue package'. In your dialogue package, make the following files:

[ol][li][iurl=#dialogueEmote]DialogueEmote.java[/li]
[li][iurl=#dialogueManager]DialogueManager.java[/li]
[li][iurl=#dialogueType]DialogueType.java[/li]
