Okay, now I am going to divide this up to four sections on what to add in each file.
[hr]
[anchor=info][b]package-info.java[/b]
You may be wondering what this java file does. This java file tells us what the package, in this case, the dialogue package, does. What's the purpose of it? You'll get told here. So, open up package-info.java and inside the file, put:
[code=java]
/**
 * Copyright Arham 4 @2013
 *
 * File made for the project Allstar-Redone.
 */
/**
 * @author Arham 4/RelentlessPK
 * Everything to do with dialogues.
 */
package dialogue;
[/code]
[hr]
[anchor=dialogueEmote][b]DialogueEmote.java[/b]
DialogueEmote.java is a file used to handle emotes/expressions in the entity's face in the dialogue box's IDs. Dialogue emotes are set via DialogueType.java. DialogueType.java's expressions are defined by YOU in DialogueManager.java.

It sounds complicated right now, but it will be easier for you later. So, just open up that DialogueEmote.java and put this code in it:
[code=java]
package dialogue;

/**
 * @author AtomicInt_
 * 
 *         Dialogue emotes.
 */
public final class DialogueEmote {

	public static final int ANGRY_1 = 614;
	public static final int ANGRY_2 = 615;
	public static final int ANGRY_3 = 616;
	public static final int ANGRY_4 = 617;
	public static final int ANNOYED = 595;
	public static final int CALM = 589;
	public static final int CALM_CONTINUED = 590;
	public static final int DEFAULT = 591;
	public static final int DELIGHTED_EVIL = 594;
	public static final int DISORIENTED_LEFT = 600;
	public static final int DISORIENTED_RIGHT = 601;
	public static final int DISTRESSED = 596;
	public static final int DISTRESSED_CONTINUED = 597;
	public static final int EVIL = 592;
	public static final int EVIL_CONTINUED = 593;
	public static final int EVIL_LAUGH_SHORT = 609;
	public static final int HAPPY = 588;
	public static final int LAUGHING = 605;
	public static final int LAUGHING_2 = 608;
	public static final int LONGER_LAUGHING = 606;
