[/code]
I'd like to thank AtomicInt_ as he had made this class for the dialogue system my server (FroyoScape) has. Let's move on!
[hr]
[anchor=dialogueManager][b]DialogueManager.java[/b]
This class really manages EVERYTHING to do with dialogues and this class is the ONLY thing you need to modify around to make a full fledged conversation! It's a very simple class, and you'll know how to make your own dialogue from the example I will provide later this tutorial.
So, open up DialogueManager.java and put this in it!
[code=java]
package dialogue;

import client;

/**
 * @author Arham 4/RelentlessPK
 * 
 *         Manages all the dialogue
 */
public class DialogueManager {

	/**
	 * The dialogue type.
	 */
	private DialogueType dialogueType = new DialogueType();

	/**
	 * Should the dialogue continue?
	 */
	private boolean continueDialogue = false;

	/**
	 * The NPC the player is talking to.
	 */
	public int npcTalkingTo = -1;

	/**
	 * Handles the dialogue depending on the npc ID.
	 * 
	 * @param player
	 *            The player.
	 * @param npcId
	 *            The NPC interacted with's ID.
	 */
	public void handleDialogue(client player, int npcId) {
		this.npcTalkingTo = npcId;
		switch (npcId) {
		}
	}

	/**
	 * Handles the "Click here to continue" packet.
	 * 
	 * @param player
	 *            The player.
	 * @param npcId
	 *            The NPC ID.
	 */
	public void handleContinueClick(client player) {
		if (continueDialogue == true) {
			System.out.println("Test.");
			player.NpcDialogue++;
			player.NpcDialogueSend = true;
			handleDialogue(player, npcTalkingTo);
		} else if (continueDialogue == false) {
			player.NpcDialogue = 0;
			player.NpcDialogueSend = false;
			npcTalkingTo = -1;
			player.closeInterface();
		}
	}

}
[/code]
